Chinese Airlines to Raise Surcharges Tomorrow, Radio Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-07T12:48:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/chinese-airlines-to-raise-surcharges-tomorrow-radio-says-1-.html
China ’s airlines will raise fuel
surcharges tomorrow after the government increased the price of
 jet fuel , China National Radio reported, without saying where it
got the information.  Surcharges will rise to 60 yuan from 50 yuan for flights of
as long as 800 kilometers and to 110 yuan from 90 yuan for
longer flights, Xinhua News Agency said separately.  The cost of No. 3 jet fuel rose by 500 yuan a ton to 6,840
yuan today, according to the National Development and Reform
Commission, the nation’s top planning agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ying Wang in Beijing at 
 ywang30@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
